        </div>
        <div class="bg-teal-900/30 border-l-[4px] border-teal-500 p-4 mt-6">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><strong class="text-teal-400">The math:</strong> Webflow-only planning: 19-39 hours. Relume + Webflow: 35-75 minutes. That's 18-38 hours saved per project. At $100/hour agency rate, that's $1,800-3,800 saved. More importantly: 0-1 missed pages vs 3-7 missed pages. Missing pages mid-project = rework = client frustration = delayed payment. Relume pays for itself on the first complex project. Simple sites (under 15 pages)? Skip Relume. Complex sites (20+ pages)? Relume is key.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
